# S06-T4: Task Detail View (Modal / Panel)
# S06-T4-TaskDetailDisplay.pd

**Objective:** Add a task detail view in totem-view that opens as a modal/overlay when a task card is selected, matching taskboard-supabase TaskDetails.vue structure and modal-glass pattern.

**Context:**
- Invariants: S05-INVARIANTS modal/overlay pattern — backdrop (fixed inset-0 bg-black/30 backdrop-blur-md z-40), panel `.modal-glass` (semi-transparent bg, blur + -webkit-backdrop-filter, border, shadow, z-50).
- Reference: `taskboard-supabase/client/src/components/modules/taskDetails/TaskDetails.vue` (visibility from selected task, backdrop + glass panel, header/content/metadata sections, close behavior).

**Gate:** LOCKED

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. Implement task detail visibility tied to selected task (composable or shared state); open when a task card is clicked, close on backdrop click or close button.
2. Render overlay: backdrop layer (dim + blur per S05-INVARIANTS) and panel layer with class `.modal-glass` (blur, border, shadow, z-50).
3. Panel content structure: header (title, close), main content (e.g. description, status), metadata section (assignee, dates, etc.) — match TaskDetails.vue sections.
4. Ensure Safari: every backdrop-filter has -webkit-backdrop-filter on the same element.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Clicking a task card opens a task detail overlay.
- Overlay uses backdrop + modal-glass panel per S05-INVARIANTS; content structure matches TaskDetails.vue.
